TEXT(beginproblem());
$showpartialcorrectanswers = 1;

$a = random(.1, .25, .03);
$b = random(1, 7,1);
$c = random(.1,1,.1);

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
A drug is injected into the bloodstream of a patient.  The concentration
of the drug in the bloodstream
(in milligrams per cubic centimeter) \(t\) hours after the injection is given by
 \[ C(t) = \frac{$a t}{t^2 + $b}. \]
Find the following instantaneous rates of change of the drug concentration with
respect to time:
$BR
(A) \( C'(.5) \) = \{ans_rule(40) \}
$BR
EOT

$ans = (((.5)**2 + $b)*($a) - (.5*$a)*(2*(.5)))/((.25 + $b)**2);
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
(B) \( C'(3) \) = \{ans_rule(40) \}
$BR
EOT

$ans = (((3)**2 + $b)*($a) - (3*$a)*(2*(3)))/((9 + $b)**2);
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

